Both deliverables are written and `transcript.json` validates against `transcript_schema.json` (25 iterations).

Headline findings:
- **Six clinical features explain ~95% of PFS variance**: feature_078 (+0.174 / unit), feature_057 (-1.15 / level), feature_013 (-0.0027), feature_006 (-0.076), feature_009 (+0.479), feature_051 (-0.376) — all p ~ 0.
- **No race or insurance disparity** (overall F p = 0.69 / 0.79 unadjusted; p = 0.978 / 0.575 adjusted).
- **Strong combination-therapy signal**: feature_109 alone → no effect; feature_039 alone → no effect; both together → **+1.44 months PFS**, p ~ 0 (n=529 dual-positive). Benefit preserved in both feature_051 strata and delivered at similar rates across racial groups (chi² p = 0.78).
- Several robust but clinically small interactions among baseline clinical features (notably feature_013 × feature_051: feature_013 prognostic weight largely vanishes when feature_051 = 1).
